    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory leak in O-RAN configuration initialization\n\n### Summary\nThe O-RAN fronthaul configuration code was allocating memory with `strdup` but never freeing it, causing memory leaks that could lead to ASN.1 encoding failures. This adds proper cleanup functions to free the allocated memory.\n\n### Changes\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.h`: Added `free_fh_init()` and `free_fh_config()` function declarations\n- `radio/fhi_72/oran-config.c`: Implemented `free_fh_init()` to properly free memory allocated by `set_fh_init()`, including:\n  - `fh_init->filePrefix` string allocated on line 612\n  - `fh_init->io_cfg.dpdk_dev[i]` strings allocated in loop on line 497\n- Added proper NULL checks and pointer nulling to prevent double-free errors\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running O-RAN fronthaul initialization repeatedly or for extended periods, memory usage would continuously increase due to unfreed strdup allocations. This could eventually lead to allocation failures or corruption during ASN.1 encoding operations that depend on available memory.\n\nThe issue manifests as:\n- Gradually increasing memory consumption during O-RAN operations\n- Potential segfaults or encoding errors in ASN.1 processing after prolonged operation\n- System instability under memory pressure\n\n"
}